==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Discontinuation
<hw>Dis`con*tin`u*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>discontinuation</ets>.]</ety> <def>Breach or interruption of
continuity; separation of parts in a connected series;
discontinuance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Upon any <qex>discontinuation</qex> of parts, made either by
bubbles or by shaking the glass, the whole mercury falls.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir I. Newton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discontinue</ent>⟦br⟧
